  "prompt": "What is production line?",
  "response": "A production line is a manufacturing process in which a product is assembled in a sequential manner through a series of workstations. Each workstation performs a specific task or adds a particular component to the product as it moves along a conveyor belt or assembly line. This method of manufacturing allows for:\n\n1. Increased efficiency\n2. Standardized production\n3. Lower labor costs\n4. Faster manufacturing times\n5. Consistent product quality\n\nProduction lines are commonly used in industries such as:\n- Automotive manufacturing\n- Electronics\n- Food processing\n- Consumer goods\n- Pharmaceuticals\n\nThe concept was popularized by Henry Ford in the early 20th century with the assembly line for automobile production, which revolutionized manufacturing by significantly reducing production time and costs.",
